---
// The counter-in-a-map bug: a live, real-`map_kernel` demonstration of the
// classic distributed-systems lost update. Two lock gauge houses keep one
// running tally in a SharedMap; concurrent read-modify-write drops a boat under
// last-write-wins. A second rig (per-replica keys summed — the PN-counter
// construction) shows why commuting writes converge, and a third runs the real
// `counter_kernel` (SharedCounter): signed delta ops, no reads at all. All rigs
// run watershed's JS-compiled Gleam kernels; rough-notation draws the attention.
---

<section id="counter-bug" class="cb" aria-label="The counter-in-a-map bug, demonstrated">
  <div class="cb-inner">
    <div class="cb-head">
      <p class="cb-lede">
        Two gauge houses at one lock keep the day's <code>boats-locked</code>
        tally in one shared map cell. Run the race and watch a boat vanish —
        then run the fix.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- ── the buggy rig ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <figure
      class="cb-rig"
      data-counter-bug="bug"
      data-caption-idle="Press “Demonstrate the bug” to race two concurrent tallies through the real map_kernel."
      data-state="idle"
    >
      <figcaption class="cb-rig-label annot">
        <span class="cb-badge cb-badge-bug">SharedMap · one shared key</span>
        <code>map_kernel · boats-locked</code>
      </figcaption>

      <div class="cb-stage">
        <div class="cb-house" data-house="a">
          <header><h3>Upstream house</h3><span class="annot">Client A</span></header>
          <div class="cb-tally">
            <span class="annot">boats-locked</span>
            <span class="cb-value" data-cell="a">41</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cb-seq-col" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="annot">sequencer</span>
          <div class="cb-seq" data-seq></div>
        </div>

        <div class="cb-house" data-house="b">
          <header><h3>Downstream house</h3><span class="annot">Client B</span></header>
          <div class="cb-tally">
            <span class="annot">boats-locked</span>
            <span class="cb-value" data-cell="b">41</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="cb-caption" data-caption aria-live="polite"></p>

      <div class="cb-verdict" data-verdict hidden>
        <div class="cb-figure">
          <span class="annot">boats actually locked</span>
          <span class="cb-fig-num" data-expected>43</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cb-figure">
          <span class="annot">tally recorded</span>
          <span class="cb-fig-num cb-fig-loss" data-recorded>42</span>
        </div>
        <p class="cb-verdict-note">
          One boat lost. LWW <strong>overwrote</strong> a read-modify-write; it
          never <strong>added</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cb-foot">
        <ol class="cb-log annot" data-log aria-label="Operation log"></ol>
        <div class="cb-controls">
          <label class="cb-pace">
            <span class="annot">Speed</span>
            <input
              type="range"
              min="0.25"
              max="1.5"
              step="0.25"
              value="0.5"
              data-cb-pace
              title="Playback speed — how fast the race plays on screen. Lower is slower; the outcome is identical at any speed."
            />
            <output data-cb-pace-out>0.5×</output>
          </label>
          <button type="button" class="cb-btn cb-btn-primary" data-play>
            Demonstrate the bug
          </button>
          <button type="button" class="cb-btn" data-reset>Reset</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </figure>

    <!-- ── the fix ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="cb-fix-copy">
      <p class="annot">Fix one · make the writes commute</p>
      <p>
        Nothing is wrong with the map — a counter just is not a single mutable
        cell. Give each replica its own key and sum them, and the two writes
        never contend. The <em>same</em> race now converges on the right total,
        through the <em>same</em> <code>map_kernel</code>. This is the classic
        per-replica-column construction (a PN-counter): it proves the principle
        that only commuting writes survive concurrency.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure
      class="cb-rig cb-rig-fix"
      data-counter-bug="fix"
      data-caption-idle="Press “Play the fix” to run the identical race with per-replica tallies."
      data-state="idle"
    >
      <figcaption class="cb-rig-label annot">
        <span class="cb-badge cb-badge-fix">Per-replica keys · sum</span>
        <code>map_kernel · boats-locked/a + boats-locked/b</code>
      </figcaption>

      <div class="cb-stage">
        <div class="cb-house" data-house="a">
          <header><h3>Upstream house</h3><span class="annot">Client A</span></header>
          <div class="cb-tally">
            <span class="annot">boats-locked · sum</span>
            <span class="cb-value" data-cell="a">41</span>
            <span class="cb-subcol">
              <span class="annot">boats-locked/a</span>
              <span class="cb-subcol-num" data-subcol="a">20</span>
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cb-seq-col" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="annot">sequencer</span>
          <div class="cb-seq" data-seq></div>
        </div>

        <div class="cb-house" data-house="b">
          <header><h3>Downstream house</h3><span class="annot">Client B</span></header>
          <div class="cb-tally">
            <span class="annot">boats-locked · sum</span>
            <span class="cb-value" data-cell="b">41</span>
            <span class="cb-subcol">
              <span class="annot">boats-locked/b</span>
              <span class="cb-subcol-num" data-subcol="b">21</span>
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="cb-caption" data-caption aria-live="polite"></p>

      <div class="cb-verdict cb-verdict-fix" data-verdict hidden>
        <div class="cb-figure">
          <span class="annot">tally recorded</span>
          <span class="cb-fig-num cb-fig-win" data-recorded>43</span>
        </div>
        <p class="cb-verdict-note">
          Both boats counted. No shared cell, no lost update.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cb-foot">
        <ol class="cb-log annot" data-log aria-label="Operation log"></ol>
        <div class="cb-controls">
          <label class="cb-pace">
            <span class="annot">Speed</span>
            <input
              type="range"
              min="0.25"
              max="1.5"
              step="0.25"
              value="0.5"
              data-cb-pace
              title="Playback speed — how fast the race plays on screen. Lower is slower; the outcome is identical at any speed."
            />
            <output data-cb-pace-out>0.5×</output>
          </label>
          <button type="button" class="cb-btn cb-btn-primary" data-play>
            Play the fix
          </button>
          <button type="button" class="cb-btn" data-reset>Reset</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </figure>

    <!-- ── the SharedCounter fix ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="cb-fix-copy">
      <p class="annot">Fix two · ship the delta</p>
      <p>
        Watershed's <a href="/structures/counters">SharedCounter</a> goes
        further: the op <em>is</em> the delta. A client never reads the tally to
        write it back — it sends <code>increment(+1)</code>, or
        <code>increment(−1)</code> for a correction, and signed deltas sum the
        same in any order. This rig runs the real
        <code>counter_kernel</code> — the SharedCounter engine itself, not a
        map at all.
      </p>
    </div>

    <figure
      class="cb-rig cb-rig-fix"
      data-counter-bug="counter"
      data-caption-idle="Press “Play the SharedCounter fix” to run the same race — plus a −1 correction — through the real counter_kernel."
      data-state="idle"
    >
      <figcaption class="cb-rig-label annot">
        <span class="cb-badge cb-badge-fix">SharedCounter · signed delta ops</span>
        <code>counter_kernel · boats-locked</code>
      </figcaption>

      <div class="cb-stage">
        <div class="cb-house" data-house="a">
          <header><h3>Upstream house</h3><span class="annot">Client A</span></header>
          <div class="cb-tally">
            <span class="annot">boats-locked</span>
            <span class="cb-value" data-cell="a">41</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="cb-seq-col" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="annot">sequencer</span>
          <div class="cb-seq" data-seq></div>
        </div>

        <div class="cb-house" data-house="b">
          <header><h3>Downstream house</h3><span class="annot">Client B</span></header>
          <div class="cb-tally">
            <span class="annot">boats-locked</span>
            <span class="cb-value" data-cell="b">41</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="cb-caption" data-caption aria-live="polite"></p>

      <div class="cb-verdict cb-verdict-fix" data-verdict hidden>
        <div class="cb-figure">
          <span class="annot">tally recorded</span>
          <span class="cb-fig-num cb-fig-win" data-recorded>43</span>
        </div>
        <p class="cb-verdict-note">
          Every delta counted — two <code>+1</code>s and a <code>−1</code>
          correction — in whatever order the sequencer picked.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cb-foot">
        <ol class="cb-log annot" data-log aria-label="Operation log"></ol>
        <div class="cb-controls">
          <label class="cb-pace">
            <span class="annot">Speed</span>
            <input
              type="range"
              min="0.25"
              max="1.5"
              step="0.25"
              value="0.5"
              data-cb-pace
              title="Playback speed — how fast the race plays on screen. Lower is slower; the outcome is identical at any speed."
            />
            <output data-cb-pace-out>0.5×</output>
          </label>
          <button type="button" class="cb-btn cb-btn-primary" data-play>
            Play the SharedCounter fix
          </button>
          <button type="button" class="cb-btn" data-reset>Reset</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </figure>

    <p class="cb-noscript" data-cb-fallback hidden>
      This demonstration needs JavaScript to run the live kernel. The takeaway:
      storing a counter in a last-write-wins map loses concurrent increments —
      use a commutative counter (watershed's
      <a href="/structures/counters">SharedCounter</a>) instead.
    </p>
    <noscript>
      <p class="cb-noscript">
        This demonstration runs a live Gleam kernel and needs JavaScript. The
        takeaway: storing a counter in a last-write-wins map loses concurrent
        increments — use a commutative <a href="/structures/counters">SharedCounter</a>.
      </p>
    </noscript>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  try {
    const { initCounterBug } = await import("../scripts/counter-bug.ts");
    initCounterBug();
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("watershed counter-bug demo failed to start", error);
    const note = document.querySelector("[data-cb-fallback]");
    if (note instanceof HTMLElement) note.hidden = false;
  }
</script>

